-- DropIndex
--
-- Made idempotent (IF EXISTS) on 2026-06-24. This migration was originally
-- generated by `prisma migrate dev` against a developer database that
-- carried `tenants_deleted_at_idx` from an earlier draft of phase10_retention.
-- The index is (re-)created cleanly by the later migration
-- `20260622120000_phase10_retention`, so on a fresh database the index does
-- not exist at this point in history and an unqualified DROP fails.
-- Embedded Postgres (the desktop track) initialises from scratch every
-- install, so this must be idempotent. Safe on existing dev/prod databases
-- too: the index was already dropped there, so IF EXISTS is a no-op.
DROP INDEX IF EXISTS "tenants_deleted_at_idx";
